atom.name: AVHS
atom.value:
Specifies if HTTP services should be started automatically on startup:
    0 = No
    1 = Yes

atom.name: AVHS
atom.value:
Specifies the desired state of the Storage services:
    10 = Offline
    20 = Read-only
    30 = Online
Changing the desired state will trigger a transition of the Storage services to the indicated state, if possible. The desired state is preserved across a restart of the service.

atom.name: AVHS
atom.value: The time limit within which a health check test must complete in order for a storage volume to be considered healthy. This time limit must be between 3 and 300 seconds (inclusive).

atom.name: AVRS
atom.value: {REGEX='^([3-9]|([1-9][0-9])|([1-2][0-9]{2})|300)$','A positive integer between 3 and 300 seconds (inclusive) is required.'}

atom.name: AVHS
atom.value:
The priority rating on the processing of foreground verification. This is the rate at which background verification takes place :

    Adaptive - Default setting. The task is designed to verify 32 TB of content in a three month period at a rate that does not exceeds 50% duty cycle (i.e., a verification rate of 4 MB/s).

    High - Storage verification proceeds quickly, at a rate that may slow ordinary grid activities. Use the High verification priority only when you suspect that a hardware or software fault may have corrupted data. After background verification has checked all stored content at a High priority, it automatically resets the priority to Adaptive.

    0 = Low (legacy)
    10 = Adaptive
    20 = High
